    ('248', 'Tyranitar', 'Rock', 'Dark', '100', '134', '110', '95', '100', '61', '600', '2.0', '202.0', '270.0', 'sand-stream|unnerve', 'unnerve', 'gen-ii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'upright', 'monster', 'mountain', 'slow', '45', '35', 'Armor PokÃ©mon', '126', 'Its body can''t be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/248.png'),
    ('249', 'Lugia', 'Psychic', 'Flying', '106', '90', '130', '90', '154', '110', '680', '5.2', '216.0', '306.0', 'pressure|multiscale', 'multiscale', 'gen-ii', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'wings', 'no-eggs', 'rare', 'slow', '3', '0', 'Diving PokÃ©mon', '127', 'It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/249.png'),
    ('250', 'Ho-Oh', 'Fire', 'Flying', '106', '130', '90', '110', '154', '90', '680', '3.8', '199.0', '306.0', 'pressure|regenerator', 'regenerator', 'gen-ii', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'wings', 'no-eggs', 'rare', 'slow', '3', '0', 'Rainbow PokÃ©mon', '128', 'Legends claim this POKÃ©MON flies the world''s skies conÂ­ tinuously on its magnificent seven- colored wings.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/250.png'),
    ('251', 'Celebi', 'Psychic', 'Grass', '100', '100', '100', '100', '100', '100', '600', '0.6', '5.0', '270.0', 'natural-cure', NULL, 'gen-ii', 'false', 'true', 'false', 'green', 'humanoid', 'no-eggs', 'forest', 'medium-slow', '45', '100', 'Time Travel PokÃ©mon', '129', 'This POKÃ©MON wanÂ­ ders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/251.png'),
    ('252', 'Treecko', 'Grass', NULL, '40', '45', '35', '65', '55', '70', '310', '0.5', '5.0', '62.0', 'overgrow|unburden', 'unburden', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'upright', 'monster|dragon', 'forest', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Wood Gecko PokÃ©mon', '130', 'TREECKO has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This POKÃ©MON attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/252.png'),
    ('253', 'Grovyle', 'Grass', NULL, '50', '65', '45', '85', '65', '95', '405', '0.9', '21.6', '142.0', 'overgrow|unburden', 'unburden', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'upright', 'monster|dragon', 'forest', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Wood Gecko PokÃ©mon', '130', 'The leaves growing out of GROVYLEâ€™s body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This POKÃ©MON is a master at climbing trees in jungles.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/253.png'),
    ('254', 'Sceptile', 'Grass', NULL, '70', '85', '65', '105', '85', '120', '530', '1.7', '52.2', '239.0', 'overgrow|unburden', 'unburden', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'upright', 'monster|dragon', 'forest', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Forest PokÃ©mon', '130', 'The leaves growing on SCEPTILEâ€™s body are very sharp edged. This POKÃ©MON is very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/254.png'),
    ('255', 'Torchic', 'Fire', NULL, '45', '60', '40', '70', '50', '45', '310', '0.4', '2.5', '62.0', 'blaze|speed-boost', 'speed-boost', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'legs', 'ground', 'grassland', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Chick PokÃ©mon', '131', 'TORCHIC sticks with its TRAINER, following behind with unsteady steps. This POKÃ©MON breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees F, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/255.png'),
    ('256', 'Combusken', 'Fire', 'Fighting', '60', '85', '60', '85', '60', '55', '405', '0.9', '19.5', '142.0', 'blaze|speed-boost', 'speed-boost', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'upright', 'ground', 'grassland', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Young Fowl PokÃ©mon', '131', 'COMBUSKEN toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out ten kicks in one second.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/256.png'),
    ('257', 'Blaziken', 'Fire', 'Fighting', '80', '120', '70', '110', '70', '80', '530', '1.9', '52.0', '239.0', 'blaze|speed-boost', 'speed-boost', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'upright', 'ground', 'grassland', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Blaze PokÃ©mon', '131', 'In battle, BLAZIKEN blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this POKÃ©MONâ€™s wrists burn.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/257.png'),
    ('258', 'Mudkip', 'Water', NULL, '50', '70', '50', '50', '50', '40', '310', '0.4', '7.6', '62.0', 'torrent|damp', 'damp', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'quadruped', 'monster|water1', 'waters-edge', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Mud Fish PokÃ©mon', '132', 'The fin on MUDKIPâ€™s head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this POKÃ©MON can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/258.png'),
    ('259', 'Marshtomp', 'Water', 'Ground', '70', '85', '70', '60', '70', '50', '405', '0.7', '28.0', '142.0', 'torrent|damp', 'damp', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'upright', 'monster|water1', 'waters-edge', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Mud Fish PokÃ©mon', '132', 'The surface of MARSHTOMPâ€™s body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This POKÃ©MON plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/259.png'),
    ('260', 'Swampert', 'Water', 'Ground', '100', '110', '90', '85', '90', '60', '535', '1.5', '81.9', '241.0', 'torrent|damp', 'damp', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'upright', 'monster|water1', 'waters-edge', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Mud Fish PokÃ©mon', '132', 'SWAMPERT is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This POKÃ©MON also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/260.png'),
    ('261', 'Poochyena', 'Dark', NULL, '35', '55', '35', '30', '30', '35', '220', '0.5', '13.6', '56.0', 'run-away|quick-feet|rattled', 'rattled', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'grassland', 'medium', '255', '70', 'Bite PokÃ©mon', '133', 'At first sight, POOCHYENA takes a bite at anything that moves. This POKÃ©MON chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/261.png'),
    ('262', 'Mightyena', 'Dark', NULL, '70', '90', '70', '60', '60', '70', '420', '1.0', '37.0', '147.0', 'intimidate|quick-feet|moxie', 'moxie', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'grassland', 'medium', '127', '70', 'Bite PokÃ©mon', '133', 'MIGHTYENA gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This POKÃ©MON will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/262.png'),
    ('263', 'Zigzagoon', 'Normal', NULL, '38', '30', '41', '30', '41', '60', '240', '0.4', '17.5', '56.0', 'pickup|gluttony|quick-feet', 'quick-feet', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'grassland', 'medium', '255', '70', 'Tiny Raccoon PokÃ©mon', '134', 'ZIGZAGOON restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This POKÃ©MON does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/263.png'),
    ('264', 'Linoone', 'Normal', NULL, '78', '70', '61', '50', '61', '100', '420', '0.5', '32.5', '147.0', 'pickup|gluttony|quick-feet', 'quick-feet', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'grassland', 'medium', '90', '70', 'Rushing PokÃ©mon', '134', 'LINOONE always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This POKÃ©MON is very challenged by gently curving roads.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/264.png'),
    ('265', 'Wurmple', 'Bug', NULL, '45', '45', '35', '20', '30', '20', '195', '0.3', '3.6', '56.0', 'shield-dust|run-away', 'run-away', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'armor', 'bug', 'forest', 'medium', '255', '70', 'Worm PokÃ©mon', '135', 'Using the spikes on its rear end,   WURMPLE peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/265.png'),
    ('266', 'Silcoon', 'Bug', NULL, '50', '35', '55', '25', '25', '15', '205', '0.6', '10.0', '72.0', 'shed-skin', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'ball', 'bug', 'forest', 'medium', '120', '70', 'Cocoon PokÃ©mon', '135', 'SILCOON tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There,  this POKÃ©MON hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/266.png'),
    ('267', 'Beautifly', 'Bug', 'Flying', '60', '70', '50', '100', '50', '65', '395', '1.0', '28.4', '178.0', 'swarm|rivalry', 'rivalry', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'yellow', 'bug-wings', 'bug', 'forest', 'medium', '45', '70', 'Butterfly PokÃ©mon', '135', 'BEAUTIFLYâ€™s favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this POKÃ©MON, just leave a potted flower by an open window. BEAUTIFLY is sure to come looking for pollen.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/267.png'),
    ('268', 'Cascoon', 'Bug', NULL, '50', '35', '55', '25', '25', '15', '205', '0.7', '11.5', '72.0', 'shed-skin', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'purple', 'ball', 'bug', 'forest', 'medium', '120', '70', 'Cocoon PokÃ©mon', '135', 'CASCOON makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This POKÃ©MON prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/268.png'),
    ('269', 'Dustox', 'Bug', 'Poison', '60', '50', '70', '50', '90', '65', '385', '1.2', '31.6', '173.0', 'shield-dust|compound-eyes', 'compound-eyes', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'bug-wings', 'bug', 'forest', 'medium', '45', '70', 'Poison Moth PokÃ©mon', '135', 'DUSTOX is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this POKÃ©MON are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/269.png'),
    ('270', 'Lotad', 'Water', 'Grass', '40', '30', '30', '40', '50', '30', '220', '0.5', '2.6', '44.0', 'swift-swim|rain-dish|own-tempo', 'own-tempo', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'armor', 'water1|plant', 'waters-edge', 'medium-slow', '255', '70', 'Water Weed PokÃ©mon', '136', 'It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/270.png'),
    ('271', 'Lombre', 'Water', 'Grass', '60', '50', '50', '60', '70', '50', '340', '1.2', '32.5', '119.0', 'swift-swim|rain-dish|own-tempo', 'own-tempo', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'humanoid', 'water1|plant', 'waters-edge', 'medium-slow', '120', '70', 'Jolly PokÃ©mon', '136', 'It lives at the waterâ€™s edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass by day and becomes active at night.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/271.png'),
    ('272', 'Ludicolo', 'Water', 'Grass', '80', '70', '70', '90', '100', '70', '480', '1.5', '55.0', '216.0', 'swift-swim|rain-dish|own-tempo', 'own-tempo', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'humanoid', 'water1|plant', 'waters-edge', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Carefree PokÃ©mon', '136', 'LUDICOLO begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This POKÃ©MON is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/272.png'),
    ('273', 'Seedot', 'Grass', NULL, '40', '40', '50', '30', '30', '30', '220', '0.5', '4.0', '44.0', 'chlorophyll|early-bird|pickpocket', 'pickpocket', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'legs', 'ground|plant', 'forest', 'medium-slow', '255', '70', 'Acorn PokÃ©mon', '137', 'SEEDOT attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this POKÃ©MONâ€™s body becomes.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/273.png'),
    ('274', 'Nuzleaf', 'Grass', 'Dark', '70', '70', '40', '60', '40', '60', '340', '1.0', '28.0', '119.0', 'chlorophyll|early-bird|pickpocket', 'pickpocket', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'humanoid', 'ground|plant', 'forest', 'medium-slow', '120', '70', 'Wily PokÃ©mon', '137', 'NUZLEAF live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This POKÃ©MON dislikes having its long nose pinched.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/274.png'),
    ('275', 'Shiftry', 'Grass', 'Dark', '90', '100', '60', '90', '60', '80', '480', '1.3', '59.6', '216.0', 'chlorophyll|wind-rider|pickpocket', 'pickpocket', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'humanoid', 'ground|plant', 'forest', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Wicked PokÃ©mon', '137', 'It lives quietly in the deep forest. It is said to create chilly winter winds with the fans it holds.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/275.png'),
    ('276', 'Taillow', 'Normal', 'Flying', '40', '55', '30', '30', '30', '85', '270', '0.3', '2.3', '54.0', 'guts|scrappy', 'scrappy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'wings', 'flying', 'grassland', 'medium-slow', '200', '70', 'Tiny Swallow PokÃ©mon', '138', 'TAILLOW courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy POKÃ©MON will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/276.png'),
    ('277', 'Swellow', 'Normal', 'Flying', '60', '85', '60', '75', '50', '125', '455', '0.7', '19.8', '159.0', 'guts|scrappy', 'scrappy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'wings', 'flying', 'grassland', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Swallow PokÃ©mon', '138', 'SWELLOW flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This POKÃ©MON dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by SWELLOWâ€™s clawed feet, preventing escape.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/277.png'),
    ('278', 'Wingull', 'Water', 'Flying', '40', '30', '30', '55', '30', '85', '270', '0.6', '9.5', '54.0', 'keen-eye|hydration|rain-dish', 'rain-dish', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'wings', 'water1|flying', 'sea', 'medium', '190', '70', 'Seagull PokÃ©mon', '139', 'WINGULL has the habit of carrying prey and valuables in its beak and hiding them in all sorts of locations. This POKÃ©MON rides the winds and flies as if it were skating across the sky.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/278.png'),
    ('279', 'Pelipper', 'Water', 'Flying', '60', '50', '100', '95', '70', '65', '440', '1.2', '28.0', '154.0', 'keen-eye|drizzle|rain-dish', 'rain-dish', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'yellow', 'wings', 'water1|flying', 'sea', 'medium', '45', '70', 'Water Bird PokÃ©mon', '139', 'It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small PokÃ©mon and eggs to safety in its bill.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/279.png'),
    ('280', 'Ralts', 'Psychic', 'Fairy', '28', '25', '25', '45', '35', '40', '198', '0.4', '6.6', '40.0', 'synchronize|trace|telepathy', 'telepathy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'humanoid', 'humanshape|indeterminate', 'urban', 'slow', '235', '35', 'Feeling PokÃ©mon', '140', 'RALTS senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This POKÃ©MON rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/280.png'),
    ('281', 'Kirlia', 'Psychic', 'Fairy', '38', '35', '35', '65', '55', '50', '278', '0.8', '20.2', '97.0', 'synchronize|trace|telepathy', 'telepathy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'humanoid', 'humanshape|indeterminate', 'urban', 'slow', '120', '35', 'Emotion PokÃ©mon', '140', 'It is said that a KIRLIA that is exposed to the positive emotions of its TRAINER grows beautiful. This POKÃ©MON controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/281.png'),
    ('282', 'Gardevoir', 'Psychic', 'Fairy', '68', '65', '65', '125', '115', '80', '518', '1.6', '48.4', '233.0', 'synchronize|trace|telepathy', 'telepathy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'humanoid', 'humanshape|indeterminate', 'urban', 'slow', '45', '35', 'Embrace PokÃ©mon', '140', 'GARDEVOIR has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its TRAINER, this POKÃ©MON is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/282.png'),
    ('283', 'Surskit', 'Bug', 'Water', '40', '30', '32', '50', '52', '65', '269', '0.5', '1.7', '54.0', 'swift-swim|rain-dish', 'rain-dish', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'armor', 'water1|bug', 'waters-edge', 'medium', '200', '70', 'Pond Skater PokÃ©mon', '141', 'From the tips of its feet, SURSKIT secretes an oil that enables it to walk on water as if it were skating. This POKÃ©MON feeds on microscopic organisms in ponds and lakes.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/283.png'),
    ('284', 'Masquerain', 'Bug', 'Flying', '70', '60', '62', '100', '82', '80', '454', '0.8', '3.6', '159.0', 'intimidate|unnerve', 'unnerve', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'bug-wings', 'water1|bug', 'waters-edge', 'medium', '75', '70', 'Eyeball PokÃ©mon', '141', 'MASQUERAIN intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns on its antennas. This POKÃ©MON flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction - even sideways and backwards - as if it were a helicopter.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/284.png'),
    ('285', 'Shroomish', 'Grass', NULL, '60', '40', '60', '40', '60', '35', '295', '0.4', '4.5', '59.0', 'effect-spore|poison-heal|quick-feet', 'quick-feet', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'legs', 'fairy|plant', 'forest', 'fast-then-very-slow', '255', '70', 'Mushroom PokÃ©mon', '142', 'SHROOMISH live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This POKÃ©MON feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/285.png'),
    ('286', 'Breloom', 'Grass', 'Fighting', '60', '130', '80', '60', '60', '70', '460', '1.2', '39.2', '161.0', 'effect-spore|poison-heal|technician', 'technician', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'upright', 'fairy|plant', 'forest', 'fast-then-very-slow', '90', '70', 'Mushroom PokÃ©mon', '142', 'BRELOOM closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s fighting technique puts boxers to shame.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/286.png'),
    ('287', 'Slakoth', 'Normal', NULL, '60', '60', '60', '35', '35', '30', '280', '0.8', '24.0', '56.0', 'truant', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'forest', 'slow', '255', '70', 'Slacker PokÃ©mon', '143', 'SLAKOTH lolls around for over twenty hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/287.png'),
    ('288', 'Vigoroth', 'Normal', NULL, '80', '80', '80', '55', '55', '90', '440', '1.4', '46.5', '154.0', 'vital-spirit', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'upright', 'ground', 'forest', 'slow', '120', '70', 'Wild Monkey PokÃ©mon', '143', 'VIGOROTH is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. It simply canâ€™t tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s stress level rises if it canâ€™t be moving constantly.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/288.png'),
    ('289', 'Slaking', 'Normal', NULL, '150', '160', '100', '95', '65', '100', '670', '2.0', '130.5', '252.0', 'truant', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'humanoid', 'ground', 'forest', 'slow', '45', '70', 'Lazy PokÃ©mon', '143', 'SLAKING spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this POKÃ©MON reluctantly moves to another spot.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/289.png'),
    ('290', 'Nincada', 'Bug', 'Ground', '31', '45', '90', '30', '30', '40', '266', '0.5', '5.5', '53.0', 'compound-eyes|run-away', 'run-away', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'armor', 'bug', 'forest', 'slow-then-very-fast', '255', '70', 'Trainee PokÃ©mon', '144', 'NINCADA lives underground for many years in complete darkness. This POKÃ©MON absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless as it waits for evolution.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/290.png'),
    ('291', 'Ninjask', 'Bug', 'Flying', '61', '90', '45', '50', '50', '160', '456', '0.8', '12.0', '160.0', 'speed-boost|infiltrator', 'infiltrator', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'yellow', 'bug-wings', 'bug', 'forest', 'slow-then-very-fast', '120', '70', 'Ninja PokÃ©mon', '144', 'NINJASK moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this POKÃ©MON was long believed to be invisible.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/291.png'),
    ('292', 'Shedinja', 'Bug', 'Ghost', '1', '90', '45', '30', '30', '40', '236', '0.8', '1.2', '83.0', 'wonder-guard', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'blob', 'mineral', 'forest', 'slow-then-very-fast', '45', '70', 'Shed PokÃ©mon', '144', 'SHEDINJAâ€™s hard body doesnâ€™t move - not even a twitch. In fact, its body appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this POKÃ©MON will steal the spirit of anyone peering into its hollow body from its back.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/292.png'),
    ('293', 'Whismur', 'Normal', NULL, '64', '51', '23', '51', '23', '28', '240', '0.6', '16.3', '48.0', 'soundproof|rattled', 'rattled', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'pink', 'upright', 'monster|ground', 'cave', 'medium-slow', '190', '70', 'Whisper PokÃ©mon', '145', 'Normally, WHISMURâ€™s voice is very quiet - it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. However, if this POKÃ©MON senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/293.png'),
    ('294', 'Loudred', 'Normal', NULL, '84', '71', '43', '71', '43', '48', '360', '1.0', '40.5', '126.0', 'soundproof|scrappy', 'scrappy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'upright', 'monster|ground', 'cave', 'medium-slow', '120', '70', 'Big Voice PokÃ©mon', '145', 'LOUDREDâ€™s bellowing can completely decimate a wood-frame house. It uses its voice to punish its foes. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s round ears serve as loudspeakers.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/294.png'),
    ('295', 'Exploud', 'Normal', NULL, '104', '91', '63', '91', '73', '68', '490', '1.5', '84.0', '221.0', 'soundproof|scrappy', 'scrappy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'upright', 'monster|ground', 'cave', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Loud Noise PokÃ©mon', '145', 'EXPLOUD triggers earthquakes with the tremors it creates by bellowing. If this POKÃ©MON violently inhales from the ports on its body, itâ€™s a sign that it is preparing to let loose a huge bellow.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/295.png'),
    ('296', 'Makuhita', 'Fighting', NULL, '72', '60', '30', '20', '30', '25', '237', '1.0', '86.4', '47.0', 'thick-fat|guts|sheer-force', 'sheer-force', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'yellow', 'humanoid', 'humanshape', 'mountain', 'fast-then-very-slow', '180', '70', 'Guts PokÃ©mon', '146', 'MAKUHITA is tenacious - it will keep getting up and attacking its foe however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this POKÃ©MON stores more energy in its body for evolving.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/296.png'),
    ('297', 'Hariyama', 'Fighting', NULL, '144', '120', '60', '40', '60', '50', '474', '2.3', '253.8', '166.0', 'thick-fat|guts|sheer-force', 'sheer-force', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'humanoid', 'humanshape', 'mountain', 'fast-then-very-slow', '200', '70', 'Arm Thrust PokÃ©mon', '146', 'It has the habit of challenging others without hesitation to tests of strength. Itâ€™s been known to stand on train tracks and stop trains using forearm thrusts.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/297.png'),
    ('298', 'Azurill', 'Normal', 'Fairy', '50', '20', '40', '20', '40', '20', '190', '0.2', '2.0', '38.0', 'thick-fat|huge-power|sap-sipper', 'sap-sipper', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'true', 'blue', 'legs', 'no-eggs', 'waters-edge', 'fast', '150', '70', 'Polka Dot PokÃ©mon', '90', 'A PokÃ©mon that lives by water. It moves quickly on land by bouncing on its big tail.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/298.png'),
    ('299', 'Nosepass', 'Rock', NULL, '30', '45', '135', '45', '90', '30', '375', '1.0', '97.0', '75.0', 'sturdy|magnet-pull|sand-force', 'sand-force', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'humanoid', 'mineral', 'cave', 'medium', '255', '70', 'Compass PokÃ©mon', '147', 'NOSEPASSâ€™s magnetic nose is always pointed to the north. If two of these POKÃ©MON meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they are close because their magnetic noses repel one another.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/299.png'),
    ('300', 'Skitty', 'Normal', NULL, '50', '45', '45', '35', '35', '50', '260', '0.6', '11.0', '52.0', 'cute-charm|normalize|wonder-skin', 'wonder-skin', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'pink', 'quadruped', 'ground|fairy', 'forest', 'fast', '255', '70', 'Kitten PokÃ©mon', '148', 'SKITTY has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This POKÃ©MON is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/300.png'),
    ('301', 'Delcatty', 'Normal', NULL, '70', '65', '65', '55', '55', '90', '400', '1.1', '32.6', '140.0', 'cute-charm|normalize|wonder-skin', 'wonder-skin', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'purple', 'quadruped', 'ground|fairy', 'forest', 'fast', '60', '70', 'Prim PokÃ©mon', '148', 'DELCATTY prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this POKÃ©MON eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/301.png'),
    ('302', 'Sableye', 'Dark', 'Ghost', '50', '75', '75', '65', '65', '50', '380', '0.5', '11.0', '133.0', 'keen-eye|stall|prankster', 'prankster', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'purple', 'humanoid', 'humanshape', 'cave', 'medium-slow', '45', '35', 'Darkness PokÃ©mon', '149', 'SABLEYE lead quiet lives deep inside caverns. They are feared, however, because these POKÃ©MON are thought to steal the spirits of people when their eyes burn with a sinister glow in the darkness.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/302.png'),
    ('303', 'Mawile', 'Steel', 'Fairy', '50', '85', '85', '55', '55', '50', '380', '0.6', '11.5', '133.0', 'hyper-cutter|intimidate|sheer-force', 'sheer-force', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'black', 'humanoid', 'ground|fairy', 'cave', 'fast', '45', '70', 'Deceiver PokÃ©mon', '150', 'MAWHILEâ€™s huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, MAWHILE chomps it with its gaping jaws.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/303.png'),
    ('304', 'Aron', 'Steel', 'Rock', '50', '70', '100', '40', '40', '30', '330', '0.4', '60.0', '66.0', 'sturdy|rock-head|heavy-metal', 'heavy-metal', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'quadruped', 'monster', 'mountain', 'slow', '180', '35', 'Iron Armor PokÃ©mon', '151', 'This POKÃ©MON has a body of steel. To make its body, ARON feeds on iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by eating bridges and rails.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/304.png'),
    ('305', 'Lairon', 'Steel', 'Rock', '60', '90', '140', '50', '50', '40', '430', '0.9', '120.0', '151.0', 'sturdy|rock-head|heavy-metal', 'heavy-metal', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'quadruped', 'monster', 'mountain', 'slow', '90', '35', 'Iron Armor PokÃ©mon', '151', 'LAIRON tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. This POKÃ©MON makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/305.png'),
    ('306', 'Aggron', 'Steel', 'Rock', '70', '110', '180', '60', '60', '50', '530', '2.1', '360.0', '239.0', 'sturdy|rock-head|heavy-metal', 'heavy-metal', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'upright', 'monster', 'mountain', 'slow', '45', '35', 'Iron Armor PokÃ©mon', '151', 'AGGRON claims an entire mountain as its own territory. It mercilessly beats up anything that violates its environment. This POKÃ©MON vigilantly patrols its territory at all times.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/306.png'),
    ('307', 'Meditite', 'Fighting', 'Psychic', '30', '40', '55', '40', '55', '60', '280', '0.6', '11.2', '56.0', 'pure-power|telepathy', 'telepathy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'humanoid', 'humanshape', 'mountain', 'medium', '180', '70', 'Meditate PokÃ©mon', '152', 'MEDITITE undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. However, whenever it meditates, this POKÃ©MON always loses its concentration and focus. As a result, its training never ends.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/307.png'),
    ('308', 'Medicham', 'Fighting', 'Psychic', '60', '60', '75', '60', '75', '80', '410', '1.3', '31.5', '144.0', 'pure-power|telepathy', 'telepathy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'humanoid', 'humanshape', 'mountain', 'medium', '90', '70', 'Meditate PokÃ©mon', '152', 'It is said that through meditation, MEDICHAM heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This POKÃ©MON hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/308.png'),
    ('309', 'Electrike', 'Electric', NULL, '40', '45', '40', '65', '40', '65', '295', '0.6', '15.2', '59.0', 'static|lightning-rod|minus', 'minus', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'grassland', 'slow', '120', '70', 'Lightning PokÃ©mon', '153', 'ELECTRIKE stores electricity in its long body hair. This POKÃ©MON stimulates its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs explosive acceleration performance.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/309.png'),
    ('310', 'Manectric', 'Electric', NULL, '70', '75', '60', '105', '60', '105', '475', '1.5', '40.2', '166.0', 'static|lightning-rod|minus', 'minus', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'yellow', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'grassland', 'slow', '45', '70', 'Discharge PokÃ©mon', '153', 'MANECTRIC is constantly discharging electricity from its mane. The sparks sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this POKÃ©MON creates thunderclouds.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/310.png'),
    ('311', 'Plusle', 'Electric', NULL, '60', '50', '40', '85', '75', '95', '405', '0.4', '4.2', '142.0', 'plus|lightning-rod', 'lightning-rod', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'yellow', 'upright', 'fairy', 'grassland', 'medium', '200', '70', 'Cheering PokÃ©mon', '154', 'PLUSLE always acts as a cheerleader for its partners. Whenever a teammate puts out a good effort in battle, this POKÃ©MON shorts out its body to create the crackling noises of sparks to show its joy.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/311.png'),
    ('312', 'Minun', 'Electric', NULL, '60', '40', '50', '75', '85', '95', '405', '0.4', '4.2', '142.0', 'minus|volt-absorb', 'volt-absorb', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'yellow', 'upright', 'fairy', 'grassland', 'medium', '200', '70', 'Cheering PokÃ©mon', '155', 'MINUN is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/312.png'),
    ('313', 'Volbeat', 'Bug', NULL, '65', '73', '75', '47', '85', '85', '430', '0.7', '17.7', '151.0', 'illuminate|swarm|prankster', 'prankster', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'upright', 'bug|humanshape', 'forest', 'slow-then-very-fast', '150', '70', 'Firefly PokÃ©mon', '156', 'With the arrival of night, VOLBEAT emits light from its tail. It communicates with others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light. This POKÃ©MON is attracted by the sweet aroma of ILLUMISE.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/313.png'),
    ('314', 'Illumise', 'Bug', NULL, '65', '47', '75', '73', '85', '85', '430', '0.6', '17.7', '151.0', 'oblivious|tinted-lens|prankster', 'prankster', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'purple', 'humanoid', 'bug|humanshape', 'forest', 'fast-then-very-slow', '150', '70', 'Firefly PokÃ©mon', '157', 'With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/314.png'),
    ('315', 'Roselia', 'Grass', 'Poison', '50', '60', '45', '100', '80', '65', '400', '0.3', '2.0', '140.0', 'natural-cure|poison-point|leaf-guard', 'leaf-guard', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'humanoid', 'fairy|plant', 'grassland', 'medium-slow', '150', '70', 'Thorn PokÃ©mon', '158', 'ROSELIA shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this POKÃ©MON brings serenity to living things.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/315.png'),
    ('316', 'Gulpin', 'Poison', NULL, '70', '43', '53', '43', '53', '40', '302', '0.4', '10.3', '60.0', 'liquid-ooze|sticky-hold|gluttony', 'gluttony', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'arms', 'indeterminate', 'grassland', 'fast-then-very-slow', '225', '70', 'Stomach PokÃ©mon', '159', 'Virtually all of GULPINâ€™s body is its stomach. As a result, it can swallow something its own size. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/316.png'),
    ('317', 'Swalot', 'Poison', NULL, '100', '73', '83', '73', '83', '55', '467', '1.7', '80.0', '163.0', 'liquid-ooze|sticky-hold|gluttony', 'gluttony', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'purple', 'arms', 'indeterminate', 'grassland', 'fast-then-very-slow', '75', '70', 'Poison Bag PokÃ©mon', '159', 'When SWALOT spots prey, it spurts out a hideously toxic fluid from its pores and sprays the target. Once the prey has weakened, this POKÃ©MON gulps it down whole with its cavernous mouth.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/317.png'),
    ('318', 'Carvanha', 'Water', 'Dark', '45', '90', '20', '65', '20', '65', '305', '0.8', '20.8', '61.0', 'rough-skin|speed-boost', 'speed-boost', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'fish', 'water2', 'sea', 'slow', '225', '35', 'Savage PokÃ©mon', '160', 'CARVANHAâ€™s strongly developed jaws and its sharply pointed fangs pack the destructive power to rip out boat hulls. Many boats have been attacked and sunk by this POKÃ©MON.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/318.png'),
    ('319', 'Sharpedo', 'Water', 'Dark', '70', '120', '40', '95', '40', '95', '460', '1.8', '88.8', '161.0', 'rough-skin|speed-boost', 'speed-boost', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'fish', 'water2', 'sea', 'slow', '60', '35', 'Brutal PokÃ©mon', '160', 'Nicknamed â€œthe bully of the sea,â€ SHARPEDO is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these POKÃ©MON can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/319.png'),
    ('320', 'Wailmer', 'Water', NULL, '130', '70', '35', '70', '35', '60', '400', '2.0', '130.0', '80.0', 'water-veil|oblivious|pressure', 'pressure', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'fish', 'ground|water2', 'sea', 'fast-then-very-slow', '125', '70', 'Ball Whale PokÃ©mon', '161', 'WAILMERâ€™s nostrils are located above its eyes. This playful POKÃ©MON loves to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body out of its nostrils.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/320.png'),
    ('321', 'Wailord', 'Water', NULL, '170', '90', '45', '90', '45', '60', '500', '14.5', '398.0', '175.0', 'water-veil|oblivious|pressure', 'pressure', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'fish', 'ground|water2', 'sea', 'fast-then-very-slow', '60', '70', 'Float Whale PokÃ©mon', '161', 'WAILORD is the largest of all identified POKÃ©MON up to now. This giant POKÃ©MON swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive amounts of food at once with its enormous mouth.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/321.png'),
    ('322', 'Numel', 'Fire', 'Ground', '60', '60', '40', '65', '45', '35', '305', '0.7', '24.0', '61.0', 'oblivious|simple|own-tempo', 'own-tempo', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'yellow', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'mountain', 'medium', '255', '70', 'Numb PokÃ©mon', '162', 'NUMEL is extremely dull witted - it doesnâ€™t notice being hit. However, it canâ€™t stand hunger for even a second. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/322.png'),
    ('323', 'Camerupt', 'Fire', 'Ground', '70', '100', '70', '105', '75', '40', '460', '1.9', '220.0', '161.0', 'magma-armor|solid-rock|anger-point', 'anger-point', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'mountain', 'medium', '150', '70', 'Eruption PokÃ©mon', '162', 'CAMERUPT has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees F courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this POKÃ©MONâ€™s back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/323.png'),
    ('324', 'Torkoal', 'Fire', NULL, '70', '85', '140', '85', '70', '20', '470', '0.5', '80.4', '165.0', 'white-smoke|drought|shell-armor', 'shell-armor', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'mountain', 'medium', '90', '70', 'Coal PokÃ©mon', '163', 'You can tell how itâ€™s feeling by the smoke spouting from its shell. Tremendous velocity is a sign of good health.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/324.png'),
    ('325', 'Spoink', 'Psychic', NULL, '60', '25', '35', '70', '80', '60', '330', '0.7', '30.6', '66.0', 'thick-fat|own-tempo|gluttony', 'gluttony', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'black', 'arms', 'ground', 'mountain', 'fast', '255', '70', 'Bounce PokÃ©mon', '164', 'SPOINK bounces around on its tail. The shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. As a result, this POKÃ©MON cannot afford to stop bouncing - if it stops, its heart will stop.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/325.png'),
    ('326', 'Grumpig', 'Psychic', NULL, '80', '45', '65', '90', '110', '80', '470', '0.9', '71.5', '165.0', 'thick-fat|own-tempo|gluttony', 'gluttony', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'purple', 'upright', 'ground', 'mountain', 'fast', '60', '70', 'Manipulate PokÃ©mon', '164', 'GRUMPIG uses the black pearls on its body to amplify its psychic power waves for gaining total control over its foe. When this POKÃ©MON uses its special power, its snorting breath grows labored.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/326.png'),
    ('327', 'Spinda', 'Normal', NULL, '60', '60', '60', '60', '60', '60', '360', '1.1', '5.0', '126.0', 'own-tempo|tangled-feet|contrary', 'contrary', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'upright', 'ground|humanshape', 'mountain', 'fast', '255', '70', 'Spot Panda PokÃ©mon', '165', 'No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/327.png'),
    ('328', 'Trapinch', 'Ground', NULL, '45', '100', '45', '45', '45', '10', '290', '0.7', '15.0', '58.0', 'hyper-cutter|arena-trap|sheer-force', 'sheer-force', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'armor', 'bug|dragon', 'rough-terrain', 'medium-slow', '255', '70', 'Ant Pit PokÃ©mon', '166', 'TRAPINCHâ€™s nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit dug in sand. This POKÃ©MON patiently waits for prey to tumble down the pit. Its giant jaws have enough strength to crush even boulders.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/328.png'),
    ('329', 'Vibrava', 'Ground', 'Dragon', '50', '70', '50', '50', '50', '70', '340', '1.1', '15.3', '119.0', 'levitate', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'bug-wings', 'bug|dragon', 'rough-terrain', 'medium-slow', '120', '70', 'Vibration PokÃ©mon', '166', 'To make prey faint, VIBRAVA generates ultrasonic waves by vigorously making its two wings vibrate. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s ultrasonic waves are so powerful, they can bring on headaches in people.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/329.png'),
    ('330', 'Flygon', 'Ground', 'Dragon', '80', '100', '80', '80', '80', '100', '520', '2.0', '82.0', '234.0', 'levitate', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'wings', 'bug|dragon', 'rough-terrain', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Mystic PokÃ©mon', '166', 'FLYGON is nicknamed â€œthe elemental  spirit of the desert.â€ Because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this POKÃ©MON is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/330.png'),
    ('331', 'Cacnea', 'Grass', NULL, '50', '85', '40', '85', '40', '35', '335', '0.4', '51.3', '67.0', 'sand-veil|water-absorb', 'water-absorb', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'humanoid', 'plant|humanshape', 'rough-terrain', 'medium-slow', '190', '35', 'Cactus PokÃ©mon', '167', 'CACNEA lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this POKÃ©MON shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/331.png'),
    ('332', 'Cacturne', 'Grass', 'Dark', '70', '115', '60', '115', '60', '55', '475', '1.3', '77.4', '166.0', 'sand-veil|water-absorb', 'water-absorb', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'humanoid', 'plant|humanshape', 'rough-terrain', 'medium-slow', '60', '35', 'Scarecrow PokÃ©mon', '167', 'During the daytime, CACTURNE remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This POKÃ©MON becomes active at night when the temperature drops.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/332.png'),
    ('333', 'Swablu', 'Normal', 'Flying', '45', '40', '60', '40', '75', '50', '310', '0.4', '1.2', '62.0', 'natural-cure|cloud-nine', 'cloud-nine', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'wings', 'flying|dragon', 'forest', 'slow-then-very-fast', '255', '70', 'Cotton Bird PokÃ©mon', '168', 'SWABLU has light and fluffy wings that are like cottony clouds. This POKÃ©MON is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/333.png'),
    ('334', 'Altaria', 'Dragon', 'Flying', '75', '70', '90', '70', '105', '80', '490', '1.1', '20.6', '172.0', 'natural-cure|cloud-nine', 'cloud-nine', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'wings', 'flying|dragon', 'forest', 'slow-then-very-fast', '45', '70', 'Humming PokÃ©mon', '168', 'ALTARIA dances and wheels through the sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this POKÃ©MON makes its listeners experience dreamy wonderment.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/334.png'),
    ('335', 'Zangoose', 'Normal', NULL, '73', '115', '60', '60', '60', '90', '458', '1.3', '40.3', '160.0', 'immunity|toxic-boost', 'toxic-boost', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'upright', 'ground', 'grassland', 'slow-then-very-fast', '90', '70', 'Cat Ferret PokÃ©mon', '169', 'Memories of battling its arch-rival SEVIPER are etched into every cell of ZANGOOSEâ€™s body. This POKÃ©MON adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/335.png'),
    ('336', 'Seviper', 'Poison', NULL, '73', '100', '60', '100', '60', '65', '458', '2.7', '52.5', '160.0', 'shed-skin|infiltrator', 'infiltrator', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'black', 'squiggle', 'ground|dragon', 'grassland', 'fast-then-very-slow', '90', '70', 'Fang Snake PokÃ©mon', '170', 'SEVIPER shares a generations-long feud with ZANGOOSE. The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. This POKÃ©MON attacks using its sword- edged tail.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/336.png'),
    ('337', 'Lunatone', 'Rock', 'Psychic', '90', '55', '65', '95', '85', '70', '460', '1.0', '168.0', '161.0', 'levitate', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'yellow', 'ball', 'mineral', 'cave', 'fast', '45', '70', 'Meteorite PokÃ©mon', '171', 'LUNATONE was discovered at a location where a meteorite fell. As a result, some people theorize that this POKÃ©MON came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/337.png'),
    ('338', 'Solrock', 'Rock', 'Psychic', '90', '95', '85', '55', '65', '70', '460', '1.2', '154.0', '161.0', 'levitate', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'ball', 'mineral', 'cave', 'fast', '45', '70', 'Meteorite PokÃ©mon', '172', 'Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins, its body shines.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/338.png'),
    ('339', 'Barboach', 'Water', 'Ground', '50', '48', '43', '46', '41', '60', '288', '0.4', '1.9', '58.0', 'oblivious|anticipation|hydration', 'hydration', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'fish', 'water2', 'waters-edge', 'medium', '190', '70', 'Whiskers PokÃ©mon', '173', 'BARBOACHâ€™s sensitive whiskers serve as a superb radar system. This POKÃ©MON hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits for prey to come along.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/339.png'),
    ('340', 'Whiscash', 'Water', 'Ground', '110', '78', '73', '76', '71', '60', '468', '0.9', '23.6', '164.0', 'oblivious|anticipation|hydration', 'hydration', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'fish', 'water2', 'waters-edge', 'medium', '75', '70', 'Whiskers PokÃ©mon', '173', 'WHISCASH is extremely territorial. Just one of these POKÃ©MON will claim a large pond as its exclusive territory. If a foe approaches it, it thrashes about and triggers a massive earthquake.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/340.png'),
    ('341', 'Corphish', 'Water', NULL, '43', '80', '65', '50', '35', '35', '308', '0.6', '11.5', '62.0', 'hyper-cutter|shell-armor|adaptability', 'adaptability', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'armor', 'water1|water3', 'waters-edge', 'fast-then-very-slow', '205', '70', 'Ruffian PokÃ©mon', '174', 'Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/341.png'),
    ('342', 'Crawdaunt', 'Water', 'Dark', '63', '120', '85', '90', '55', '55', '468', '1.1', '32.8', '164.0', 'hyper-cutter|shell-armor|adaptability', 'adaptability', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'armor', 'water1|water3', 'waters-edge', 'fast-then-very-slow', '155', '70', 'Rogue PokÃ©mon', '174', 'CRAWDAUNT has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this POKÃ©MON, making them desolate places.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/342.png'),
    ('343', 'Baltoy', 'Ground', 'Psychic', '40', '40', '55', '40', '70', '55', '300', '0.5', '21.5', '60.0', 'levitate', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'arms', 'mineral', 'rough-terrain', 'medium', '255', '70', 'Clay Doll PokÃ©mon', '175', 'BALTOY moves while spinning around on its one foot. Primitive wall paintings depicting this POKÃ©MON living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/343.png'),
    ('344', 'Claydol', 'Ground', 'Psychic', '60', '70', '105', '70', '120', '75', '500', '1.5', '108.0', '175.0', 'levitate', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'black', 'arms', 'mineral', 'rough-terrain', 'medium', '90', '70', 'Clay Doll PokÃ©mon', '175', 'CLAYDOL are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. This POKÃ©MON moves about while levitating.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/344.png'),
    ('345', 'Lileep', 'Rock', 'Grass', '66', '41', '77', '61', '87', '23', '355', '1.0', '23.8', '71.0', 'suction-cups|storm-drain', 'storm-drain', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'purple', 'blob', 'water3', 'sea', 'slow-then-very-fast', '45', '70', 'Sea Lily PokÃ©mon', '176', 'LILEEP became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient POKÃ©MON attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles  shaped like flower petals.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/345.png'),
    ('346', 'Cradily', 'Rock', 'Grass', '86', '81', '97', '81', '107', '43', '495', '1.5', '60.4', '173.0', 'suction-cups|storm-drain', 'storm-drain', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'blob', 'water3', 'sea', 'slow-then-very-fast', '45', '70', 'Barnacle PokÃ©mon', '176', 'CRADILY roams around the ocean floor in search of food. This POKÃ©MON freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/346.png'),
    ('347', 'Anorith', 'Rock', 'Bug', '45', '95', '50', '40', '50', '75', '355', '0.7', '12.5', '71.0', 'battle-armor|swift-swim', 'swift-swim', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'armor', 'water3', 'waters-edge', 'slow-then-very-fast', '45', '70', 'Old Shrimp PokÃ©mon', '177', 'ANORITH was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. This primitive POKÃ©MON once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/347.png'),
    ('348', 'Armaldo', 'Rock', 'Bug', '75', '125', '100', '70', '80', '45', '495', '1.5', '68.2', '173.0', 'battle-armor|swift-swim', 'swift-swim', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'upright', 'water3', 'waters-edge', 'slow-then-very-fast', '45', '70', 'Plate PokÃ©mon', '177', 'ARMALDOâ€™s tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/348.png'),
    ('349', 'Feebas', 'Water', NULL, '20', '15', '20', '10', '55', '80', '200', '0.6', '7.4', '40.0', 'swift-swim|oblivious|adaptability', 'adaptability', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'fish', 'water1|dragon', 'waters-edge', 'slow-then-very-fast', '255', '70', 'Fish PokÃ©mon', '178', 'FEEBASâ€™s fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this POKÃ©MON is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/349.png'),
    ('350', 'Milotic', 'Water', NULL, '95', '60', '79', '100', '125', '81', '540', '6.2', '162.0', '189.0', 'marvel-scale|competitive|cute-charm', 'cute-charm', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'pink', 'squiggle', 'water1|dragon', 'waters-edge', 'slow-then-very-fast', '60', '70', 'Tender PokÃ©mon', '178', 'Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/350.png'),
    ('351', 'Castform', 'Normal', NULL, '70', '70', '70', '70', '70', '70', '420', '0.3', '0.8', '147.0', 'forecast', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'ball', 'fairy|indeterminate', 'grassland', 'medium', '45', '70', 'Weather PokÃ©mon', '179', 'CASTFORMâ€™s appearance changes with the weather. This POKÃ©MON gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/351.png'),
    ('352', 'Kecleon', 'Normal', NULL, '60', '90', '70', '60', '120', '40', '440', '1.0', '22.0', '154.0', 'color-change|protean', 'protean', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'upright', 'ground', 'forest', 'medium-slow', '200', '70', 'Color Swap PokÃ©mon', '180', 'It changes body color to blend in with its surroundings. It also changes color if it is happy or sad.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/352.png'),
    ('353', 'Shuppet', 'Ghost', NULL, '44', '75', '35', '63', '33', '45', '295', '0.6', '2.3', '59.0', 'insomnia|frisk|cursed-body', 'cursed-body', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'black', 'ball', 'indeterminate', 'urban', 'fast', '225', '35', 'Puppet PokÃ©mon', '181', 'SHUPPET is attracted by feelings of jealousy and vindictiveness. If someone develops strong feelings of vengeance, this POKÃ©MON will appear in a swarm and line up beneath the eaves of that personâ€™s home.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/353.png'),
    ('354', 'Banette', 'Ghost', NULL, '64', '115', '65', '83', '63', '65', '455', '1.1', '12.5', '159.0', 'insomnia|frisk|cursed-body', 'cursed-body', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'black', 'upright', 'indeterminate', 'urban', 'fast', '45', '35', 'Marionette PokÃ©mon', '181', 'BANETTE generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This POKÃ©MON was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/354.png'),
    ('355', 'Duskull', 'Ghost', NULL, '20', '40', '90', '30', '90', '25', '295', '0.8', '15.0', '59.0', 'levitate|frisk', 'frisk', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'black', 'arms', 'indeterminate', 'forest', 'fast', '190', '35', 'Requiem PokÃ©mon', '182', 'DUSKULL can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this POKÃ©MON chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/355.png'),
    ('356', 'Dusclops', 'Ghost', NULL, '40', '70', '130', '60', '130', '25', '455', '1.6', '30.6', '159.0', 'pressure|frisk', 'frisk', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'black', 'humanoid', 'indeterminate', 'forest', 'fast', '90', '35', 'Beckon PokÃ©mon', '182', 'DUSCLOPSâ€™s body is completely hollow - there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This POKÃ©MON will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/356.png'),
    ('357', 'Tropius', 'Grass', 'Flying', '99', '68', '83', '72', '87', '51', '460', '2.0', '100.0', '161.0', 'chlorophyll|solar-power|harvest', 'harvest', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'green', 'quadruped', 'monster|plant', 'forest', 'slow', '200', '70', 'Fruit PokÃ©mon', '183', 'The bunches of fruit around TROPIUSâ€™s neck are very popular with children. This POKÃ©MON loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/357.png'),
    ('358', 'Chimecho', 'Psychic', NULL, '75', '50', '80', '95', '90', '65', '455', '0.6', '1.0', '159.0', 'levitate', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'arms', 'indeterminate', 'grassland', 'fast', '45', '70', 'Wind Chime PokÃ©mon', '184', 'CHIMECHO makes its cries echo inside its hollow body. When this POKÃ©MON becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have the power to knock foes flying.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/358.png'),
    ('359', 'Absol', 'Dark', NULL, '65', '130', '60', '75', '60', '75', '465', '1.2', '47.0', '163.0', 'pressure|super-luck|justified', 'justified', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'quadruped', 'ground', 'mountain', 'medium-slow', '30', '35', 'Disaster PokÃ©mon', '185', 'Every time ABSOL appears before people, it is followed by a disaster such as an earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the disaster POKÃ©MON.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/359.png'),
    ('360', 'Wynaut', 'Psychic', NULL, '95', '23', '48', '23', '48', '23', '260', '0.6', '14.0', '52.0', 'shadow-tag|telepathy', 'telepathy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'true', 'blue', 'upright', 'no-eggs', 'cave', 'medium', '125', '70', 'Bright PokÃ©mon', '100', 'WYNAUT can always be seen with a big, happy smile on its face. Look at its tail to determine if it is angry. When angered, this POKÃ©MON will be slapping the ground with its tail.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/360.png'),
    ('361', 'Snorunt', 'Ice', NULL, '50', '50', '50', '50', '50', '50', '300', '0.7', '16.8', '60.0', 'inner-focus|ice-body|moody', 'moody', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'humanoid', 'fairy|mineral', 'cave', 'medium', '190', '70', 'Snow Hat PokÃ©mon', '186', 'SNORUNT live in regions with heavy snowfall. In seasons without snow, such as spring and summer, this POKÃ©MON steals away to live quietly among stalactites and stalagmites deep in caverns.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/361.png'),
    ('362', 'Glalie', 'Ice', NULL, '80', '80', '80', '80', '80', '80', '480', '1.5', '256.5', '168.0', 'inner-focus|ice-body|moody', 'moody', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'ball', 'fairy|mineral', 'cave', 'medium', '75', '70', 'Face PokÃ©mon', '186', 'GLALIE has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This POKÃ©MON has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/362.png'),
    ('363', 'Spheal', 'Ice', 'Water', '70', '40', '50', '55', '50', '25', '290', '0.8', '39.5', '58.0', 'thick-fat|ice-body|oblivious', 'oblivious', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'fish', 'water1|ground', 'sea', 'medium-slow', '255', '70', 'Clap PokÃ©mon', '187', 'SPHEAL is much faster rolling than  walking to get around. When groups of this POKÃ©MON eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/363.png'),
    ('364', 'Sealeo', 'Ice', 'Water', '90', '60', '70', '75', '70', '45', '410', '1.1', '87.6', '144.0', 'thick-fat|ice-body|oblivious', 'oblivious', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'fish', 'water1|ground', 'sea', 'medium-slow', '120', '70', 'Ball Roll PokÃ©mon', '187', 'SEALEO has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This POKÃ©MON occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a SPHEAL on its nose.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/364.png'),
    ('365', 'Walrein', 'Ice', 'Water', '110', '80', '90', '95', '90', '65', '530', '1.4', '150.6', '239.0', 'thick-fat|ice-body|oblivious', 'oblivious', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'quadruped', 'water1|ground', 'sea', 'medium-slow', '45', '70', 'Ice Break PokÃ©mon', '187', 'It swims through icy seas while shattering ice floes with its large tusks. It is protected by its thick blubber.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/365.png'),
    ('366', 'Clamperl', 'Water', NULL, '35', '64', '85', '74', '55', '32', '345', '0.4', '52.5', '69.0', 'shell-armor|rattled', 'rattled', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'ball', 'water1', 'sea', 'slow-then-very-fast', '255', '70', 'Bivalve PokÃ©mon', '188', 'CLAMPERLâ€™s sturdy shell is not only good for protection - it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown CLAMPERLâ€™s shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/366.png'),
    ('367', 'Huntail', 'Water', NULL, '55', '104', '105', '94', '75', '52', '485', '1.7', '27.0', '170.0', 'swift-swim|water-veil', 'water-veil', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'squiggle', 'water1', 'sea', 'slow-then-very-fast', '60', '70', 'Deep Sea PokÃ©mon', '188', 'HUNTAILâ€™s presence went unnoticed by people for a long time because it lives at extreme depths in the sea. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s eyes can see clearly even in the murky dark depths of the ocean.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/367.png'),
    ('368', 'Gorebyss', 'Water', NULL, '55', '84', '105', '114', '75', '52', '485', '1.8', '22.6', '170.0', 'swift-swim|hydration', 'hydration', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'pink', 'squiggle', 'water1', 'sea', 'slow-then-very-fast', '60', '70', 'South Sea PokÃ©mon', '188', 'GOREBYSS lives in the southern seas at extreme depths. Its body is built to withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of this, this POKÃ©MONâ€™s body is unharmed by ordinary attacks.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/368.png'),
    ('369', 'Relicanth', 'Water', 'Rock', '100', '90', '130', '45', '65', '55', '485', '1.0', '23.4', '170.0', 'swift-swim|rock-head|sturdy', 'sturdy', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'fish', 'water1|water2', 'sea', 'slow', '25', '70', 'Longevity PokÃ©mon', '189', 'RELICANTH is a POKÃ©MON species that existed for a hundred million years without ever changing its form. This ancient POKÃ©MON feeds on microscopic organisms with its toothless mouth.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/369.png'),
    ('370', 'Luvdisc', 'Water', NULL, '43', '30', '55', '40', '65', '97', '330', '0.6', '8.7', '116.0', 'swift-swim|hydration', 'hydration', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'pink', 'fish', 'water2', 'sea', 'fast', '225', '70', 'Rendezvous PokÃ©mon', '190', 'LUVDISC live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped POKÃ©MON earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the oceanâ€™s waves.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/370.png'),
    ('371', 'Bagon', 'Dragon', NULL, '45', '75', '60', '40', '30', '50', '300', '0.6', '42.1', '60.0', 'rock-head|sheer-force', 'sheer-force', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'humanoid', 'dragon', 'rough-terrain', 'slow', '45', '35', 'Rock Head PokÃ©mon', '191', 'Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/371.png'),
    ('372', 'Shelgon', 'Dragon', NULL, '65', '95', '100', '60', '50', '50', '420', '1.1', '110.5', '147.0', 'rock-head|overcoat', 'overcoat', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'white', 'quadruped', 'dragon', 'rough-terrain', 'slow', '45', '35', 'Endurance PokÃ©mon', '191', 'Inside SHELGONâ€™s armor-like shell, cells are in the midst of transformation to create an entirely new body. This POKÃ©MONâ€™s shell is extremely heavy, making its movements sluggish.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/372.png'),
    ('373', 'Salamence', 'Dragon', 'Flying', '95', '135', '80', '110', '80', '100', '600', '1.5', '102.6', '270.0', 'intimidate|moxie', 'moxie', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'quadruped', 'dragon', 'rough-terrain', 'slow', '45', '35', 'Dragon PokÃ©mon', '191', 'SALAMENCE came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this POKÃ©MONâ€™s cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/373.png'),
    ('374', 'Beldum', 'Steel', 'Psychic', '40', '55', '80', '35', '60', '30', '300', '0.6', '95.2', '60.0', 'clear-body|light-metal', 'light-metal', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'blob', 'mineral', 'rough-terrain', 'slow', '3', '35', 'Iron Ball PokÃ©mon', '192', 'Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic force courses throughout BELDUMâ€™s body. This POKÃ©MON communicates with others by sending controlled pulses of magnetism.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/374.png'),
    ('375', 'Metang', 'Steel', 'Psychic', '60', '75', '100', '55', '80', '50', '420', '1.2', '202.5', '147.0', 'clear-body|light-metal', 'light-metal', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'arms', 'mineral', 'rough-terrain', 'slow', '3', '35', 'Iron Claw PokÃ©mon', '192', 'When two BELDUM fuse together, METANG is formed. The brains of the BELDUM are joined by a magnetic nervous system. By linking its brains magnetically, this POKÃ©MON generates strong psychokinetic power.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/375.png'),
    ('376', 'Metagross', 'Steel', 'Psychic', '80', '135', '130', '95', '90', '70', '600', '1.6', '550.0', '270.0', 'clear-body|light-metal', 'light-metal', 'gen-iii', 'false', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'heads', 'mineral', 'rough-terrain', 'slow', '3', '35', 'Iron Leg PokÃ©mon', '192', 'METAGROSS has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This POKÃ©MON can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/376.png'),
    ('377', 'Regirock', 'Rock', NULL, '80', '100', '200', '50', '100', '50', '580', '1.7', '230.0', '261.0', 'clear-body|sturdy', 'sturdy', 'gen-iii', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'brown', 'humanoid', 'no-eggs', 'cave', 'slow', '3', '35', 'Rock Peak PokÃ©mon', '193', 'Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/377.png'),
    ('378', 'Regice', 'Ice', NULL, '80', '50', '100', '100', '200', '50', '580', '1.8', '175.0', '261.0', 'clear-body|ice-body', 'ice-body', 'gen-iii', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'humanoid', 'no-eggs', 'cave', 'slow', '3', '35', 'Iceberg PokÃ©mon', '194', 'REGICEâ€™s body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body canâ€™t be melted, even by fire. This POKÃ©MON controls frigid air of minus 328 degrees F.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/378.png'),
    ('379', 'Registeel', 'Steel', NULL, '80', '75', '150', '75', '150', '50', '580', '1.9', '205.0', '261.0', 'clear-body|light-metal', 'light-metal', 'gen-iii', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'gray', 'humanoid', 'no-eggs', 'cave', 'slow', '3', '35', 'Iron PokÃ©mon', '195', 'REGISTEEL has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this POKÃ©MON eats.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/379.png'),
    ('380', 'Latias', 'Dragon', 'Psychic', '80', '80', '90', '110', '130', '110', '600', '1.4', '40.0', '270.0', 'levitate', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'red', 'wings', 'no-eggs', 'waters-edge', 'slow', '3', '90', 'Eon PokÃ©mon', '196', 'LATIAS is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this POKÃ©MON ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/380.png'),
    ('381', 'Latios', 'Dragon', 'Psychic', '80', '90', '80', '130', '110', '110', '600', '2.0', '60.0', '270.0', 'levitate', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'wings', 'no-eggs', 'waters-edge', 'slow', '3', '90', 'Eon PokÃ©mon', '197', 'LATIOS has the ability to make its foe see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This POKÃ©MON is intelligent and understands human speech.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/381.png'),
    ('382', 'Kyogre', 'Water', NULL, '100', '100', '90', '150', '140', '90', '670', '4.5', '352.0', '302.0', 'drizzle', NULL, 'gen-iii', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'blue', 'fish', 'no-eggs', 'sea', 'slow', '3', '0', 'Sea Basin PokÃ©mon', '198', 'KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours. This POKÃ©MON saved people who were suffering from droughts.', 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/382.png'),
